at the time of the violation of section 39 - 10 - 71 the motor vehicle was in the possession of a
lessee, and the lessor provides a peace officer with the motor vehicle's registration number
and the name, address, and operator's license number of the individual renting or leasing the
motor vehicle.
5. An individual may not be charged both with violating this section and section 39 - 10 - 71 for acts
arising out of the same incident or occurrence.
6. This section may not apply to a motor vehicle rental company that rents motor vehicles to
customers for a period of ninety days or less.

